publishedDatasources.name: Job Performance
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: Job Performance contains events and runtime information for background jobs initiated by scheduled tasks on the site. Jobs include extract refreshes, flow runs, and Bridge refreshes.

*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data corresponds to a unique background job and the related content item, providing information about job status, duration, and error details.

publishedDatasources.name: Permissions
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: Permissions contains the effective permissions for all users and content on the site.
*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data corresponds to a combination of user, content item, and permission capability.

publishedDatasources.name: TS Users
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: TS Users contains data about your users such as remaining licenses, site roles, and content ownership metrics.

*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data corresponds to a unique User on your Tableau Online site.

publishedDatasources.name: Viz Load Times
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: Viz Load Times contains the load time information for views on your site.

*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data corresponds to a request for a content item and the load duration, measured in seconds.

publishedDatasources.name: Groups
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: Groups identifies the group membership of users. Groups without members, and users not in a group, will be included as a row of data with null values represented as "NULL".

*What is a Row of Data?* There is one row of data for each unique combination of group and user pairing.

publishedDatasources.name: Subscriptions
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: Subscriptions contains detailed information for subscriptions on the site, such as creator and recipient, content item name, job status, and schedules. A user following a Pulse metric is also considered a subscription for this data source.
*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data represents a user who is subscribed to a view or follows a Pulse metric.

publishedDatasources.name: Site Content
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: Site Content provides essential governance information about the projects, data sources, workbooks, and views on a site. The data provided about a content item may be unique to its item type. Item types with unique fields are in folders with titles that correspond to their Item Type.

_Note_: Users that connect to the Site Content data source will see data about all content items on the site, regardless of the permissions set for each item. Keep this in mind if you plan to distribute to non-administrative users.

*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data corresponds to a unique content item. Item LUID is the unique identifier for content items on a Tableau Online pod.

publishedDatasources.name: Tokens
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: Tokens contains information about active, unexpired user tokens on the site, including personal access tokens (PATs), refresh tokens, and OAuth tokens. The data source allows site administrators to monitor token usage, ensuring that necessary tokens are renewed.

*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data corresponds to a combination of Token ID and Owner Email.

publishedDatasources.name: superstore_transactions
publishedDatasources.description: Transactional dataset updated daily with sales, product and inventory data

publishedDatasources.name: TS Events
publishedDatasources.description:
*Overview*: TS Events functions as a primary audit data source. It contains data about various events happening on your site, including sign-ins, publishes, and accessed views.

*What is a Row of Data?* Each row of data correlates with a single event that occurs on the Tableau Online site.
